  "texts": [
    "We hypothesize that the concepts of positive and negative in the sentiment analysis context are universal, and the concept of neutral enters the space of custom classes.",
    "Hence the model finds it easy to give biased answers towards these 2 classes.The order in which the examples are presented biases the output.",
    "When performing the error analysis of both zero-shot and few-shot approaches we found out that each one has a different bias towards one specific class.",
    "We then experimented variations of the prompt, by inverting the order in which the classes are enumerated and the examples are presented.",
    "We did not observe major changes in performance for any of the classes for the zero-shot approach, which means the order in which the possible classes are enumerated does not have a big impact on the output."
  ],
